.TH GIT-RANGE-DIFF-REMOTE "1" "March 2026" "git-range-diff-remote git-range-diff-remote" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-range-diff-remote \- range-diff local commits against a PR's remote state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git
\fI\,range-diff-remote \/\fR[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]... [\fI\,RANGE-DIFF-OPTION\/\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compare local commits against the remote version of the current pull request
using git\-range\-diff(1).
.PP
In the default mode the "old" side is the pushed remote ref (@{push}) and the
"new" side is local HEAD. Useful for reviewing local changes before pushing.
.PP
With \fB\-\-since\-ack\fR the "old" side is the commit you last ACK'd (or utACK'd) in a
PR comment. Useful when re\-reviewing a PR after a force\-push.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-since\-ack\fR
range\-diff from last ACK'd commit instead of @{push}
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
display this help and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
output version information and exit
.PP
Any unrecognised options (e.g. \fB\-\-creation\-factor\fR, \fB\-\-no\-color\fR) are forwarded
to git\-range\-diff(1).
.PP
Requirements: git, gh, jq
